Package it.unipr.sowide.actodes.service.logging

Provides classes defining the components of the logging service. This service supports the retrieval and storing of the relevant events describing the execution of an application.
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Wrapper<T>
    The Wrapper interface defines a wrapper for logging the activities of actor components.
    Writer
    The Writer interface defines logging records writers.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BinaryReader
    The BinaryReader defines a reader for binary logging files.
    BinaryWriter
    The BinaryWriter defines a binary writer performing its output on a file.
    ConsoleWriter
    The ConsoleWriter defines a textual writer performing its output on the console.
    DispatcherWrapper
    The DispatcherWrapper class wraps a dispatcher to support the logging of its activities.
    LogFilter
    The CycleProcessing interface identifies some logging record filters that refines the filtering on the basis of the Log objects contained in the records.
    Logger
    The Logger class logs information about the activities of an actor space.
    RegistryWrapper
    The RegistryWrapper class wraps a registry to support the logging of its activities.
    SocketReader
    The SoxketReader defines a reader for binary logging information coming from one or more socket writers.
    SocketWriter
    The SocketWriter defines a writer performing its output on a TCP socket.
    StorerWrapper
    The StorerWrapper class wraps a storer to support the logging of its activities.
    TextualFormatter
    The TextualFormatter class provides the methods for formatting logging messages in a human readable format.
    TextualWriter
    The TextualWriter defines a textual writer performing its output on a file.
